RACE.RACE_TEXT: ASSINIBOIA DOWNS RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 10200. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUTCOME cleared early and came over into the two-path, dueled outside to final turn, dueled inside final turn, opened up eighth pole, held well. TARA TATTOO bumped with JUSTA BUSTER into the first turn, pressed outside, dueled three-wide final turn, turned back eighth pole, kept coming. RUNAWAY HURRICANE stalked duel outside, rallied. JUSTA BUSTER bumped with TARA TATTOO into the first turn when UNCLE MO'S CAT steadied inside of him, stalked duel off rail, made a bid bid between horses on the final turn, was turned back nearing the eighth pole. UNCLE MO'S CAT steadied into first turn when PIONEER TOWN came through to his inside and came over, stalked duel inside, finished evenly. PIONEER TOWN moved through inside into first turn bothering UNCLE MO'S CAT, dueled inside, gave way into the final turn. PEB showed little. The rider aboard JUSTA BUSTER lodged a claim of foul against the rider of the winner for interference into the first turn. There was no change.
